E%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%AD%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to stroke with the hand or similar, to wipe off, to sweep"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to anoint"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to smooth, to polish"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to wipe off, to wipe out, to cross off, to erase, to scrub, to flush"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to wear, to fatigate, to emaciate","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to survey, to scan for proportions by going over, to clear through, to peragrate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to wipe off, to anoint","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to Christianize","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of مَسَحَ (masaḥa)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a survey"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"main route"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a coarse cloth, sackcloth, gunny, haircloth","examples":[{"text":"وَأَوَّلُ مَنْ يَدْخُلُ عَلَيْهَا إِذَا قَدِمَ فَاطِمَةَ فَقَدِمَ مِنْ غَزَاةٍ لَهُ وَقَدْ عَلَّقَتْ مِسْحًا أَوْ سِتْرًا عَلَى بَابِهَا وَحَلَّتِ الْحَسَنَ وَالْحُسَيْنَ قُلْبَيْنِ مِنْ فِضَّةٍ فَقَدِمَ فَلَمْ يَدْخُلْ فَظَنَّتْ أَنَّ مَا مَنَعَهُ أَنْ يَدْخُلَ مَا رَأَى فَهَتَكَتِ السِّتْرَ وَفَكَّكَتِ الْقُلْبَيْنِ عَنِ الصَّبِيَّيْنِ وَقَطَعَتْهُ بَيْنَهُمَا","english":"The first he visited on his return was Fāṭima, and he retourned from a raid and she had hung up a gunny or some drapery at her door, and bedecked al-Ḥasan and al-Ḥusayn by using silver bracelets. So, when he arrived, he entered not. And she believed he was barred from entering by what he had seen, so she tore down the drapery, unfastened the bracelets from the boys and cut them off."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cilice, haircloth"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Ugaritic 𐎎𐎌𐎈 (mšḥ) and Hebrew מָשַׁח (mašáḥ, “to anoint”).\n\nThis could be taken as from the root م س ح (m s ḥ) above as for a wiping rag, however the cloths denoted by this word do not seem to have been adapted for such an employment, and their property of coarseness makes the term adverse to that root’s meanings for smoothness. Therefore a connection to Coptic ⲙⲟϫϩ (mojh, “girdle of a soldier or monk”) or a related word is suggested."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n38560","headword_ar":"مَسْحٌ","root":"msH","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balaAsN","text_ar":"بَلَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) i.e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A garment of thick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coarse, hair-cloth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the T: and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of such stuff as is spread in a house"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"blAs","text_ar":"بلاس"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is worn by monks:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kisaA='","text_ar":"كِسَا=ء"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of hair-cloth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an old and worn-out garment:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kull:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amosaAHN","text_ar":"اَمْسَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musuwHN","text_ar":"مُسُوحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) the former a pl. of pauc., and the latter a pl. of mult. (L.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misoHN","text_ar":"مِسْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"main part, and middle, of a road;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAd~apN","text_ar":"جَادَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amosaAHN","text_ar":"اَمْسَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musuwHN","text_ar":"مُسُوحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","Mgh","L","Kull","K"]},{"entry_id":"n38561","headword_a